The paper discusses the influence of phase noise on CO-OFDM systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of software-based FFT multiplexing and demultiplexing techniques also suggests a possible category of optimization and control (cs.OH). The paper also discusses the impact of dispersion on the RF pilot tone, which is related to signal processing (cs.SI) and physical-layer communication (cs.PF).
